{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "# Transformation with Missing Values\n",
    "\n",
    "You may use an Image with **NaN** as missing values."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib.image import imread\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import ImageGrid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Read Image and cast type\n",
    "\n",
    "Note that `NaN` values can only be assigned to `float` like arrays."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ar = imread(\"../data/image.jpg\")[100:200, 100:200]\n",
    "ar = ar.astype(np.float64)"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Create artificial hole, missing data"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ar[40:-40, 40:-40] = np.nan\n",
    "plt.imshow(ar / 256)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Image with NaN Hole\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Transform & Plot Transformation\n",
    "\n",
    "Notice how GLCM works around the hole.\n",
    "\n",
    "- For GLCM Windows that are totally **NaN**s, the result is a **NaN**.\n",
    "- For GLCM Windows that partially contain **NaN**s, the result is the GLCM of the non-NaN values"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "GLCM Progress: 100%|| 106k/106k [00:00<00:00, 257k Cells/s] \n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "Text(0.5, 0.98, 'Padded GLCM Features (Cube Rooted for visibility)')"
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 864x576 with 18 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from glcm_cupy import glcm\n",
    "\n",
    "radius = 2\n",
    "step_size = 1\n",
    "g = glcm(ar, bin_from=256, bin_to=16, radius=radius, step_size=step_size)\n",
    "# Plot in a grid\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "grid = ImageGrid(fig, 111,\n",
    "                 nrows_ncols=(3, 3),\n",
    "                 axes_pad=0.4)\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, f_ix, title in zip(grid, range(g.shape[-1]),\n",
    "                           (\"HOMOGENEITY\", \"CONTRAST\", \"ASM\", \"MEAN\",\n",
    "                            \"VARIANCE\", \"CORRELATION\", \"DISSIMILARITY\"), ):\n",
    "    ax.imshow(g[..., f_ix] ** (1 / 3))\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Padded GLCM Features (Cube Rooted for visibility)')"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  }
 ],
